OL,3,CCouncil workers face industrial action
OL,4,Cballot after pay offer rejected
OL,6,FUnite general secretary Sharon Graham
OL,7,Fsaid: "Our members undertake vital
OL,8,Ffrontline roles that ensure that local
OL,9,Fcommunities are well maintained, safe
OL,10,Fand attractive places to live, they
OL,11,Fhave drawn a line in the sand and will
OL,12,Fnot accept any further erosion of
OL,13,Ftheir pay."
OL,15,FAn industrial action ballot will begin
OL,16,Fon August 30 and Unite said if there
OL,17,Fis a yes vote, strikes could begin
OL,18,Flater this autumn.
